# Firebase Hosting — deploy after changes

The live site is **Firebase Hosting** (`firebase deploy`, project `child-consultant`, URL https://child-consultant.web.app). The owner expects the **hosted build to be updated whenever web-facing work is finished** in a session.

## When to deploy

- After you finish edits that affect the **static app** (especially anything under `public/`, including HTML/CSS/JS the portal serves).
- Run deploy **before** telling the user work is complete, unless they explicitly asked **not** to deploy for this task.

## Command

From the repo root:

```bash
firebase deploy --only hosting
```

Use `full_network` (or equivalent) if the tool environment blocks outbound calls.

## Do not conflate with Git

- **Hosting deploy** = what makes https://child-consultant.web.app show new code.
- **`git push`** = only when the user asks; do not push by default.

## If deploy fails

Report the error (e.g. not logged in to Firebase CLI). Do not claim the site is updated until deploy succeeds.
